The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sehwag gets past Kapil
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Sehwag gets past Kapil
                      
	Virender Sehwag, after hitting four sixes against England on Sunday, now has the record of hitting most sixes (64 sixes) among Indians in Tests. He went past Kapil Dev, who had hit 61 sixes.               
	Following is the list of Indians with most sixes in Test cricket:         
	Virender Sehwag 64 sixes (65 Tests, 112 innings)         
	Kapil Dev 61 sixes (131 Tests, 184 innings)         
	Sourav Ganguly 57 sixes (113 Tests, 188 innings)         
	Sachin Tendulkar 47 sixes (154 Tests, 252 innings)         
	Navjot Singh Sidhu 38 sixes (51 Tests, 78 innings)         
	Mahendra Singh Dhoni 32 (33 Tests, 53 innings)           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                      
